{"name": "aqora-cli", "metadata": {"name": "aqora-cli", "version": "0.10.0", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://github.com/aqora-io/cli", "dependencies": ["uv"], "summary": "The aqora command line interface", "upload_time": 1733574524}, "documentation": ["# Installation\n\nTo install the CLI, you can use pip. Note that the CLI requires Python 3.9 or greater\n\n```bash\n# with pip\npip install aqora-cli\n\n# with pipx\npipx install aqora-cli\n\n# on Windows with Python installed from python.org\npy -m pip install aqora-cli\n\n# on Windows with Python installed from the Windows Store\npython -m pip install aqora-cli\n```\n\n## Notes for Windows users\n\nIf pip gives you a warning that the script is not on your PATH, you can copy the\ndirectory in the warning and add it to your path by [following the instructions\nhere](https://www.java.com/en/download/help/path.html)\n\nYou may also need to install the latest Visual C++ Redistributable Version. You\ncan find [the latest version here](https://learn.microsoft.com/cpp/windows/latest-supported-vc-redist?view=msvc-170#latest-microsoft-visual-c-redistributable-version)\n\n# Getting Started\n\nTo verify the installation, the following should output helpful information\n\n```bash\naqora help\n```\n\nOnce the CLI has installed you can login to your account with the following command\n\n```bash\naqora login\n```\n\nBrowse the competitions on [aqora.io](https://aqora.io) and climb the leaderboards!\n\n# Contributing\n\nWe strongly recommend you to install a stable Rust toolchain using [Rustup](https://rustup.rs/), and a\n[stable Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) runtime through official distributions.\n\nOur main branch is called `main`. Please open a pull-request up-to-date to that branch\nwhen you request our feedback.\n\nPlease follow [Conventional\nCommits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/), which allows our\nproject to have beautiful changelogs based on your commit messages. We strongly\nencourage you to install [Cocogitto](https://docs.cocogitto.io/):\n\n```bash\n$ cargo install cocogitto cargo-edit\n$ cog install-hook --all\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.test", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.test.solution", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "_", "type": {"name": "Input", "xref": {"fqname": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.test.use_case.Input", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Output", "xref": {"fqname": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.test.use_case.Output", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.Input", "xref": {"fqname": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.use_case.Input", "project": null}}, {"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.Output", "xref": {"fqname": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.use_case.Output", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.use_case", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.use_case.generator", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "_", "type": {"name": "PipelineConfig", "xref": {"fqname": "aqora_cli.PipelineConfig", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "AsyncIterator", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.AsyncIterator", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Input", "xref": {"fqname": "Input", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "template.assets.use_case.use_case.use_case.aggregate", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "outputs", "type": {"name": "AsyncIterator", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.AsyncIterator", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "EvaluationResults", "xref":